          "distractors": ["来れば", "考え方は", "正して"],
          "alts": [],
          "explanation": "<b>～たら</b> expresses a conditional in time sequence: 'when/if X happens.' <b>～なければいけません</b> expresses obligation: 'must / have to.'"
        },
        {
          "kind": "scramble",
          "q": "If you are going to study literature, this document is important.",
          "segments": ["文学を", "勉強するなら", "この", "文書が", "大切です"],
          "distractors": ["文学は", "勉強すれば", "文書を"],
          "alts": [],
          "explanation": "<b>～なら</b> is a contextual conditional: 'if that is the case / given that you plan to do X.' It responds to a known situation or stated plan."
        },
        {
          "kind": "scramble",
          "q": "If you want to correct your way of thinking, it is better to read good literature.",
